	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Clones may:
<br />
<br />-have poor signal routing to the cart connector such as tying VRAM /CE to /CA13 on the PCB which will break "four-screen" games
<br />
<br />-have differences in the PPU fetch logic or timing which would break some MMC5 features (Castlevania III would still work however)
<br />
<br />-not have the same reset characteristics (Phi2 = Hi-Z) which IIRC is used for bootstrapping and resetting back to the menu

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


